title: American Horror Stories: Episode 1 & 2 Review "Rubber (Wo)man"
author: Reel Talk
comment: Ryan needs to lay off the coke and sit down with a wider range of story writers and make a solid story line instead of just showing people getting killed when u need some action
These two episodes feel like some teenage girls fanfic that got put on screen
Honestly, it might be the worst writing and the worst acting I've ever seen. Hollywood is dead and haunting all of us.

The black eyes were confusing, Ruby is a little annoying. The concept of the girls humiliating scarlet was great, but the dad with blonde hair is an ass and just unclear why they focused so much on him, there was too much going on
description:
American Horror Stories: Episode 1 & 2 Review "Rubber (Wo)man." Okay, where to begin? This was a good start to the series, but it has its bad moments. Let's discuss!
